body:
I have setup sparkleshare-dashboard and added repository in config like this

exports.folders = [
  { type: 'git', name: 'Public GIT folder', path: 'C:/Users/DELL/SparkleShare/test4/.git', pub: true }
];

And then i link the device by adding host address "https://github.com" and link code,generated by sparkle-share dashboard but i it show only blank screen on android side.

I've set up the dashboard but I think I haven't configured the folders correctly in the config.js:

exports.folders = [
  { type: 'git', name: 'Development', path: '/sync/development.git', pub: false },
  { type: 'git', name: 'Documents', path: '/sync/documents.git', pub: false },
  { type: 'git', name: 'Pictures', path: '/sync/pictures.git', pub: false },
  { type: 'git', name: 'Share', path: '/sync/share.git', pub: false }
];

Does this look right - when I connect my Android to the server it connects but shows a blank screen?
